From Henry Spencer Subject Re Moonbase race In article C TM msu edu Tom writes On the other hand, if Apollo cost billion, for a few days or weeks in space, in dollars, then won't the reward have to be a lot more than only billion to get any takers Apollo was done the hard way, in a big hurry, from a very limited technology base and on government contracts Just doing it privately, rather than as a government project, cuts costs by a factor of several All work is one man's work Henry Spencer U of Toronto Zoology Kipling utzoo henry